wari: The Palmleaf From Uk\u016b B\u0101h\u0101h NS 235/AD 1114 | first = Kamal P. | last = Malla | author-link = Kamal P. Malla | journal = Kailash | volume = 16 | issue = 1\u20132 | year = 1990 | pages = 15\u201326 | url = https://www.repository.cam.ac.uk/handle/1810/227444 }}</ref> ||\n|-\n| {{0|{{circa|lk=no}}}}&nbsp;1138\u20131153 || [[Jurchen language|Jurchen]] || stele in [[Kyongwon County|Kyongwon]]<ref>{{cite book | title = The Sino-Jurchen Vocabulary of the Bureau of Interpreters | first = Daniel | last = Kane | publisher = Research Institute for Inner Asian Studies, Indiana University | year = 1989 | isbn = 978-0-933070-23-3 | page = 59 }}</ref> || [[Aisin-Gioro Ulhicun]] has identified an inscription found on the [[Arkhara River]] as Jurchen and dated it to 1127.\n|-\n| {{0|{{circa|lk=no}}}}&nbsp;1160\u20131170 || [[Middle Dutch]] || ''Het Leven van Sint Servaes'' (\"Life of [[Saint Servatius]]\") by [[Heinrich von Veldeke]]<ref>Willemyns (2013), p. 50.</ref> ||\n|-\n| {{circa|lk=no}} 1175 || [[Galician-Portuguese]] || ''[[wikisource:pt:Not\u00edcia de Fiadores|Not\u00edcia de Fiadores]]''<ref>{{cite web | title = Documentos relativos a Soeiro Pais, Urraca Mendes, sua mulher, e a Paio Soares Romeu, seu segundo filho e Not\u00edcia de Fiadores | publisher = [[Torre do Tombo National Archive]] | year = 2008 | url = http://digitarq.arquivos.pt/details?id=4380613 | access-date = 4 April 2017 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20171115223503/http://digitarq.arquivos.pt/details?id=4380613 | archive-date = 15 November 2017 | url-status = dead }}</ref> || The ''[[Not\u00edcia de Torto]]'' and the will of [[Afonso II of Portugal]], dated 1214, are often cited as the first documents written in Galician-Portuguese.<ref>{{cite book |title= Portuguese: A Linguistic Introduction |first= Milton M. |last= Azevedo |publisher= Cambridge University Press |year= 2005 |isbn= 978-0-521-80515-5 |pages= 177\u2013178 }}</ref> A date prior to 1175 has been proposed for t