na]] ||\n|-\n| {{0|{{circa|lk=no}}}} 1521 || [[Romanian language|Romanian]] || [[Neac\u0219u's Letter]] || Cyrillic orthographic manual of Constantin Kostentschi from 1420 documents earlier written usage.<ref>''Istoria Romaniei in Date'' (1971), p. 87</ref> Four 16th century documents, namely ''Codicele Voronetean'', ''Psaltirea Scheiana'', ''Psaltirea Hurmuzachi'' and ''Psaltirea Voroneteana'', are arguably copies of 15th century originals.<ref>{{cite book | first = Eugeen | last = Roegiest | title = Vers les sources des langues romanes: un itin\u00e9raire linguistique \u00e0 travers la Romania | publisher = ACCO | year = 2006 | isbn = 978-90-334-6094-4 | page = 136}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{0|{{circa|lk=no}}}} 1530 || [[Latvian language|Latvian]] || Nicholas Ramm's translation of a hymn ||\n|-\n| {{0|{{circa|lk=no}}}} 1535 || [[Estonian language|Estonian]] || Wanradt-Koell catechism ||\n|-\n| {{0|{{circa|lk=no}}}} 1536 || Modern [[Portuguese language|Portuguese]] || ''[[wikisource:pt:Galeria:Grammatica da lingoagem portuguesa (1536).pdf|Grammatica da lingoagem portuguesa]]'' by [[Fern\u00e3o de Oliveira]]. || by convention.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://ler.letras.up.pt/uploads/ficheiros/4584.pdf |title=A categoria gramatical de g\u00e9nero do portugu\u00eas antigo ao portugu\u00eas actual |last1=Frias e Gouveia |first1=Maria Carmen de |date=2005 |publisher=Faculdade de Letras da Universidade do Porto}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{0|{{circa|lk=no}}}} 1549 || [[Sylheti language|Sylheti]] || Talib Husan by Ghulam Husan || earliest extant manuscript found using the [[Sylheti Nagri]] script.<ref name=\"bpedia\">{{cite book |last=Islam |first=Muhammad Ashraful |year=2012 |chapter=Sylheti Nagri |chapter-url=http://en.banglapedia.org/index.php?title=Sylheti_Nagri |editor1-last=Islam |editor1-first=Sirajul |editor1-link=Sirajul Islam |editor2-last=Jamal |editor2-first=Ahmed A. |title=Banglapedia: National Encyclopedia of Bangladesh |edition=Second |publisher=[[Asiatic Society of Bangladesh]]}}</r