 D.S. | editor-surname = Anderson | publisher = Routledge | year = 2008 | isbn = 978-0-415-32890-6 }}</ref> ||\n|-\n| {{0|{{circa|lk=no}}}} 1851 || [[Sakha language|Sakha (Yakut)]] || ''\u00dcber die Sprache der Jakuten'', a grammar by [[Otto von B\u00f6htlingk]] || Wordlists were included in ''Noord en Oost Tartarije'' (1692) by [[Nicolaas Witsen]] and ''Das Nord-und Ostliche Theil von Europa und Asia'' (1730) by [[Philip Johan von Strahlenberg]].\n|-\n| {{0|{{circa|lk=no}}}} 1854 || [[Inari Sami language|Inari Sami]] || grammar by [[Elias L\u00f6nnrot]] || Primer and catechism published in 1859.\n|-\n| {{0|{{circa|lk=no}}}} 1856 || [[Gamilaraay language|Gamilaraay]] || articles by [[William Ridley (Presbyterian missionary)|William Ridley]]<ref>{{cite book | first = Peter K. | last = Austin | chapterurl = http://www.hrelp.org/aboutus/staff/peter_austin/AustinGamil.pdf | chapter = The Gamilaraay (Kamilaroi) Language, northern New South Wales \u2014 A Brief History of Research | pages = 37\u201358 | title = Encountering Aboriginal languages: studies in the history of Australian linguistics | editor-first = William | editor-last = McGregor | publisher = Australian National University | year = 2008 | isbn = 978-0-85883-582-5}}</ref> || Basic vocabulary collected by [[Thomas Mitchell (explorer)|Thomas Mitchell]] in 1832.\n|-\n| {{0|{{circa|lk=no}}}} 1872 || [[Venda language|Venda]] || reduced to writing by the Berlin Missionaries || First complete [[Bible]] translation 1936\n|-\n| {{0|{{circa|lk=no}}}} 1878 || [[Kildin Sami]] || Gospel of Matthew ||\n|-\n| {{0|{{circa|lk=no}}}} 1882 || [[Mirandese]] || ''O dialecto mirandez'' by [[Jos\u00e9 Leite de Vasconcelos]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://mirandes.no.sapo.pt/LMdescoberta.html |title=A descoberta do mirand\u00eas \u2013 Marcos principais |last=Ferreira |first=M. Barros |website=S\u00edtio de l Mirand\u00e9s |publisher=Universidade de Lisboa |location=Lisbon |language=Portuguese |url-status=bot: unknown |archiveurl=https