 Isabirye to Somalia head coach job|url=http://www.kawowo.com/index.php/football/item/29167-mawa-beats-isabirye-to-somalia-head-coach-job.html|website=Kawowo.com|accessdate=5 November 2016|date=5 November 2016}}</ref>\n| {{flagicon|UGA}}\n| Nov 2016 \u2013\n| 2\n| 0\n| 0\n| 2\n| 0%\n|-\n|}\n\n==Recent schedule and results==\n{{main|Somalia national football team results}}\nThe following is a list of match results from the previous 12 months, as well as any future matches that have been scheduled.\n\n{{legend2|#CCFFCC|'''W'''<small>in</small>|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#FFFFCC|'''D'''<small>raw</small>|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#FFCCCC|'''L'''<small>oss</small>|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n\n===2019===\n{{footballbox collapsible\n| round        = [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification \u2013 CAF First Round|2022 FIFA World Cup Qualification - 1st round]]\n| date         = {{Start date|2019|09|05|df=y}}\n| team1        = {{fb-rt|Somalia}}\n| score        = 1\u20130\n| report       = https://www.goal.com/en/news/african-world-cup-qualifying-billiat-less-zimbabwe-stunned/123e75qirb1yv1jk40ye812bb0\n| team2        = {{fb|Zimbabwe}}\n| goals1       = \n* [[Anwar Shakunda|Shakunda]] {{goal|87}}\n| stadium      = [[El Hadj Hassan Gouled Aptidon Stadium]]\n| location     = [[Djibouti City]], [[Djibouti]]{{refn|group=note|Played in Djibouti due to security concerns from the [[Somali Civil War|ongoing civil war]]}}\n| attendance   = \n| result       = W\n}}\n{{footballbox collapsible\n|round        = [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification \u2013 CAF First Round|2022 FIFA World Cup Qualification - 1st round]]\n|date         = {{Start date|2019|09|10|df=y}}\n|time       = {{UTZ|15:00|2}}\n|team1      = {{fb-rt|ZIM}}\n|score      = 3\u20131\n|aggregatescore = 3\u20132\n|team2      = {{fb|SOM}}\n|goals1     =\n*[[Marshall Munetsi|Munetsi]] {{goal|77}}\n*[[Admiral Muskwe|Muskwe]] {{goal|86}}\n*[[Khama Billiat|Billiat]] {{goal|90}}\n|goals2     =\n*[[Omar Mohamed|Mohamed]] {{goal|85}}\n|stadium    = [[National Sports Stadium (Zimbabwe)|National Sports Stadium]]\n|location   = [[Harare]], [[Zimbabwe]]\n|attendance =\n|referee    = Andofetra Rakotojaona ([[Malagasy Football Federation|Madagascar]])\n|report     = [https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/qatar2022/preliminaries/africa/matches/match/400087255/ Report (FIFA)]\n|result     = L\n}}\n\n[[File:Somalia national team drills for 2018WCQ.jpg|thumbnail|The national team doing drills as part of preparations for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup qualification|2018 FIFA World Cup qualifiers]]]]\n\n==Competitive record==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===FIFA World Cup record===\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n!colspan=9|[[FIFA World Cup|FIFA World Cup record]]\n!width=1% rowspan=39|\n!colspan=6|[[FIFA World Cup qualification|FIFA World Cup Qualification record]]\n|-\n!Year\n!Round\n!Position\n!{{Tooltip|Pld|Games played}}\n!{{Tooltip|W|Won}}\n!{{Tooltip|D|Drawn}}*\n!{{Tooltip|L|Lost}}\n!{{Tooltip|GF|Goals for}}\n!{{Tooltip|GA|Goals against}}\n!{{Tooltip|Pld|Games played}}\n!{{Tooltip|W|Won}}\n!{{Tooltip|D|Drawn}}\n!{{Tooltip|L|Lost}}\n!{{Tooltip|GF|Goals for}}\n!{{Tooltip|GA|Goals against}}\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Uruguay}} [[1930 FIFA World Cup|1930]]\n|colspan=8 rowspan=6|''Part of [[Italy national football team|Italy]] & UK''\n|colspan=6 rowspan=6|''Part of [[Italy national football team|Italy]] & UK''\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Italy|1861}} [[1934 FIFA World Cup|1934]]\n|-\n|{{flagicon|France}} [[1938 FIFA World Cup|1938]]\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Brazil|1889}} [[1950 FIFA World Cup|1950]]\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Switzerland}} [[1954 FIFA World Cup|1954]]\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Sweden}} [[1958 FIFA World Cup|1958]]\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Chile}} [[1962 FIFA World Cup|1962]]\n|colspan=8 rowspan=5|''Did not enter''\n|colspan=6 rowspan=5|''Did not enter''\n|-\n|{{flagicon|England}} [[1966 FIFA World Cup|1966]]\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Mexico}} [[1970 FIFA World Cup|1970]]\n|-\n|{{flagicon|West Germany}} [[1974 FIFA World C