ofs damaged and windows blown out; one structure attached to the church was severely damaged as most of its roof was ripped off and its south-facing wall collapsed. Two buildings saw sheet metal peeled away, while one of the structures had its metal roof purlins bent. Several homes suffered significant roof damage and saw windows blown out; one had its garage door collapsed. Trees were snapped or uprooted.\n|<ref>{{cite report|agency=National Weather Service Weather Forecast Office in Fort Worth, Texas|title=Texas Event Report: EF1 Tornado|url=https://www.ncdc.noaa.gov/stormevents/eventdetails.jsp?id=856475|publisher=National Centers for Environmental Information|year=2019|accessdate=January 21, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|bgcolor={{storm colour|cat2}} | EF2\n|[[Garland, Texas|Garland]]\n|[[Dallas County, Texas|Dallas]]\n|[[Texas|TX]]\n|{{Coord|32.8974|-96.6753|name=Garland (Oct. 20, EF2)}}\n|{{Sort|005|October&nbsp;20}}\n|02:24\u201302:30\n|{{convert|2.48|mi|km|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|{{convert|265|yd|m|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|A wide section of the roof to a Sear's Facility warehouse was peeled off, tearing away the adjacent metal walls and causing some of the interior support columns and beams to bend. An empty 18-wheeler and a van were tipped onto their sides. Nearby, a newly-built warehouse collapsed as its support columns were bent to the ground; debris from this structure caused additional damage to nearby homes. Along the remainder of the tornado path, numerous residences suffered roof damage and many trees were snapped or uprooted.\n|<ref>{{cite report|agency=National Weather Service Weather Forecast Office in Fort Worth, Texas|title=Texas Event Report: EF2 Tornado|url=https://www.ncdc.noaa.gov/stormevents/eventdetails.jsp?id=856477|publisher=National Centers for Environmental Information|year=2019|accessdate=January 21, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|bgcolor={{storm colour|cat1}} | EF1\n|[[Rowlett, Texas|Rowlett]]\n|[[Dallas County, Texas|Dallas]]\n|[[Texas|TX]]\n|{{Coord|32.9237|-96.5697|name=Rowlett (Oct. 20, EF1)}}\n|{{Sort|006|October&nbsp;20}}\n|02:36\u201302:45\n|{{convert|6.02|mi|km|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|{{convert|500|yd|m|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|This tornado severely damaged a house near PGBT while damaging several others. It also destroyed several barns and outbuildings.\n|<ref>{{cite report|agency=National Weather Service Weather Forecast Office in Fort Worth, Texas|title=Texas Event Report: EF1 Tornado|url=https://www.ncdc.noaa.gov/stormevents/eventdetails.jsp?id=856502|publisher=National Centers for Environmental Information|year=2019|accessdate=January 21, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|bgcolor={{storm colour|storm}} | EF0\n|W of [[Ferris, Texas|Ferris]]\n|[[Ellis County, Texas|Ellis]]\n|[[Texas|TX]]\n|{{Coord|32.5332|-96.6664|name=Ferris (Oct. 20, EF0)}}\n|{{Sort|007|October&nbsp;20}}\n|02:42\u201302:44\n|{{convert|0.18|mi|km|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|{{convert|170|yd|m|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|A silo was damaged and partially collapsed, multiple businesses sustained roof damage, a power pole was downed, and trees were snapped or uprooted.\n|<ref>{{cite report|agency=National Weather Service Weather Forecast Office in Fort Worth, Texas|title=Texas Event Report: EF0 Tornado|url=https://www.ncdc.noaa.gov/stormevents/eventdetails.jsp?id=856503|publisher=National Centers for Environmental Information|year=2019|accessdate=January 21, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|bgcolor={{storm colour|cat1}} | EF1\n|[[Rockwall, Texas|Rockwall]]\n|[[Rockwall County, Texas|Rockwall]]\n|[[Texas|TX]]\n|{{Coord|32.9312|-96.4864|name=Rockwall (Oct. 20, EF1)}}\n|{{Sort|008|October&nbsp;20}}\n|02:48\u201302:54\n|{{convert|1.96|mi|km|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|{{convert|100|yd|m|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|Several homes suffered significant roof damage. Trees and fences were downed.\n|<ref>{{cite report|agency=National Weather Service Weather Forecast Office in Fort Worth, Texas|title=Texas Event Report: EF1 Tornado|url=https://www.ncdc.noaa.gov/stormevents/eventdetails.jsp?id=856504|